      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 23
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Up for sale is a driver-spec 2011 BMW M3 featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This engine utilizes eight individual throttle bodies to deliver instantaneous throttle response and a linear power band peaking at its 8,400 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution during high-lateral-G cornering. This example remains mechanically sharp; the VANOS system is quiet, and preventative maintenance including rod bearing replacement and throttle actuator service has been addressed. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, and the hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback enthusiasts crave. While the finish shows light stone chipping and minor bolster wear, the drivetrain and suspension geometry are dialed-in for immediate performance.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 23
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used car. Good condition. Well-maintained. Clean title. Ready for immediate sale.",
