    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for the discerning enthusiast is this 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This naturally aspirated powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear 333 hp power band with an 8,000 RPM redline. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a reinforced rear subframe and refreshed bushings throughout the multi-link rear suspension. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution and corner-exit traction. Recent preventative maintenance includes rod bearing replacement and a shim-and-bucket valve adjustment, ensuring internal tolerances remain within factory specifications. While the exterior shows the honest patina of a well-enjoyed driver, the mechanical integrity is prioritized, featuring a cooling system overhaul and stainless steel brake lines for consistent pedal feel. This is a robustly maintained example of BMW's high-revving peak, ready for the B-roads.",
      "price": 34500.0,
